article.headline: Bradley 92, Northeastern 86
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. (AP) -- Phillip Gilbert scored 23 points as Bradley defeated Northeastern 92-86 Sunday in the second round of the Las Vegas Tournament. Gilbert was one of five players who scored in double figures for Bradley (2-0). Marcellus Sommerville scored 20 points and grabbed a game-high 13 rebounds. Mike Suggs added 15 points and Marcello Robinson and Jason Faulknor each chipped in 11. The Braves outrebounded the Huskies 53-37 and shot 47 percent from the field, compared to 41 percent for Northeastern. The Huskies (0-2) were led by Marcus Barnes' 20 points. Javorie Wilson and Jose Barea each had 18 points, and Gene Oliynyk added 14.
